## 2026-04-04 - No cross-set token move — atomic "Move to set…" action
- Feature already fully implemented. No changes needed.
- The context menu "Move to set..." button in TokenTreeNode.tsx calls `onRequestMoveToken` → `handleRequestMoveToken` (useTokenCrud.ts) → opens a modal (TokenListModals.tsx) → calls `POST /api/tokens/:set/tokens/move` → `TokenStore.moveToken()` atomically moves the token and saves both sets → `operationLog.record()` logs it for undo.
- Alias references don't need rewriting because the token path stays identical across sets — alias resolution (`flatTokens`) covers all sets, so `{path}` refs continue to resolve correctly after a move.

